Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.78,0:00:06.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the perfect place for a drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.98,0:00:11.74,Kei,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Nakanishi Kei \NResort Inn Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.34,0:00:09.02,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The locals are proud of this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.02,0:00:11.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's an impressive two-lane road, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.18,0:00:14.85,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,You chose the perfect day for your visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.20,0:00:20.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't tagged along, this \Nwould've been the best drive ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:22.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan asked me to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.70,0:00:25.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She asked me to make sure \Nyou didn't cut loose too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.35,0:00:33.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just having Nakanishi \NKei-san show me around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.74,0:00:35.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:39.60,ToDo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the car — fun conversation \NLunch — warm up to each other \NAmusement park? — build excitement! \NSunset at the beach — passionate conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:41.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You brat! Give that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.94,0:00:43.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You stole this, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.20,0:00:45.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You dropped it on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:47.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's a "passionate conversation," anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.09,0:00:48.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You drew a heart next to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.47,0:00:51.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.55,0:00:52.61,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,That's hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.84,0:00:53.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:57.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you seem to be over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.18,0:00:59.49,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,All thanks to you, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.97,0:01:03.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were unusually helpful \Nfor once during her case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.46,0:01:04.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was the very first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:06.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.32,0:01:08.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, the light's green.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.96,0:01:10.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.44,0:01:15.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.40,0:01:17.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With brilliant detective \Nskills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.00,0:01:20.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the third wheel on a three-person drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.15,0:01:22.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where will the cheerful conversation lead us?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.37,0:01:26.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.09,0:01:28.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:13.96,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(404,1)}Turning Point on a Driving Date
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.84,0:03:11.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Turning Point on a Driving Date!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.45,0:03:18.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was six months ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.12,0:03:18.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.97,0:03:21.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to Haido-kitamachi for work,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.28,0:03:23.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to come across it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.25,0:03:30.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}A woman named Kirisaki Remi was \Nfound hanging in her own apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.76,0:03:30.48,Remi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kirisaki Remi (30) \NKei's Neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.77,0:03:34.98,Kiyomi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Fukurai Kiyomi (58) \NApartment Landlady
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.84,0:03:34.01,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}She moved in three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.01,0:03:39.49,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}She'd been mentioning all the time \Nsince then that she wanted to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:42.69,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,She said the same thing to me several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.17,0:03:46.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,On top of the landlady and \NNakanishi Kei-san's testimony,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.49,0:03:50.50,Will,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Will  \NI'm tired of living, so I'm \Ngoing to the other world \NKirisaki Remi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.73,0:03:48.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,they found a note left by the woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:50.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was clearly a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:55.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The signature even matched the lease she \Nsigned when she moved into the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.02,0:04:00.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But concerning her neighbor's \Ndeath, Kei-san said...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.73,0:04:02.00,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.52,0:04:06.01,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't prevent her suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.53,0:04:08.76,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.06,0:04:10.14,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.14,0:04:13.06,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's the one who made the final \Ndecision to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:15.48,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.53,0:04:20.70,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san's words saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:23.78,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,So I sent him a thank you letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:29.29,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Right now I'm helping out at the resort \Ninn operated by my uncle and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.78,0:04:32.41,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great place with \Nmountains and beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.41,0:04:35.30,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're ever in the area, \NI hope you'll stop by.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.09,0:04:38.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you shamelessly showed up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.79,0:04:40.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Shamelessly?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:43.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:46.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on? There \Nwasn't any traffic before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.90,0:04:52.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But, Kei-san, why did Kirisaki-san's \Nsuicide bother you so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.57,0:04:54.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were just neighbors, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:56.19,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:04:59.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them were good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.76,0:05:01.32,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.88,0:05:06.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,About a week later, I \Nreturned to the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.78,0:05:08.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see how you were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.76,0:05:11.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you'd already moved by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.72,0:05:14.03,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I had been planning to move \Nsince before the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.03,0:05:16.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the landlady told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.65,0:05:19.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when she told me about the fire, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:21.34,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how you knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:22.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.63,0:05:26.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There was a small fire near the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:28.71,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fire, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.19,0:05:30.01,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:34.02,Kirisaki,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Kirisaki
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.42,0:05:31.70,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.70,0:05:33.14,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.20,0:05:35.07,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.61,0:05:40.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was surprised to see you\Ncome out of Kirisaki-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:42.40,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,While I was visiting,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.74,0:05:45.19,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Kirisaki-san left when she realized \Nshe had forgotten something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.19,0:05:48.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And you ended up holding down the fort.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.97,0:05:52.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since they were used to coming and going \Nfrom each other's rooms, it's no surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.81,0:05:57.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural you were shocked \Nby Kirisaki-san's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:58.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.14,0:06:01.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Watch where you're going, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:05.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's that look for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.79,0:06:07.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Bleh to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.64,0:06:10.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Kids don't even do that these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.62,0:06:19.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why did Kirisaki Remi-san \Nwant to kill herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:21.92,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I asked her, too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.49,0:06:25.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The day after the article on her \Nsuicide appeared in the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.37,0:06:27.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,a man visited the apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.54,0:06:30.00,DCItalic,KAMATARI,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure it was her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.00,0:06:31.03,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:36.54,Eiji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kamatari Eiji (32) \NFinancial Company Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.50,0:06:36.54,DCItalic,KAMATARI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}So this is where that debt-avoiding \Nwoman fled to this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.82,0:06:39.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, she killed \Nherself because she was tired
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.50,0:06:41.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,of running from debt collectors all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.72,0:06:43.27,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.27,0:06:45.87,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, I finally learned the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:49.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's just conveying the landlady's story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:51.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I know even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.94,0:06:56.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since two years ago, she'd \Nbeen using a fake names.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.96,0:07:01.19,DCItalic,KAMATARI,0000,0000,0000,,Hayashi Mayuko, Wada Miyuki, Inuyama Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:02.69,DCItalic,KAMATARI,0000,0000,0000,,She'd been using all kinds of names!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.90,0:07:06.70,DCItalic,KAMATARI,0000,0000,0000,,And even though that brassy woman \Nwouldn't pay off her debts,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.70,0:07:08.94,DCItalic,KAMATARI,0000,0000,0000,,she'd play pachinko all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.19,0:07:11.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She'd been using fake names \Nsince two years earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:15.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did she use her real \Nname to rent that apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.91,0:07:17.70,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:21.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And mister, "brassy" doesn't \Nmatch the description
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.07,0:07:27.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,given by Kei-san and the landlady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.62,0:07:30.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was definitely Kirisaki Remi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.56,0:07:35.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The relatives the police called confirmed \Nit was her and took the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.28,0:07:38.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then it couldn't have been a stand-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.56,0:07:39.95,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,What an interesting boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.95,0:07:42.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's just a cheeky brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.64,0:07:42.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.68,0:07:46.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's a police checkpoint?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.51,0:07:50.74,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to bother you while you're in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:54.24,Tan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Yamazumi Tan (35) \NPolice Officer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.96,0:07:53.22,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There was a robbery in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:54.24,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:07:57.12,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit was a mustachioed well-built man,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:08:00.04,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,who fled in a white sedan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.26,0:08:02.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That fits perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:05.51,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get out of the car without \Nany resistance, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.51,0:08:07.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, wait! I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:09.64,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.14,0:08:12.22,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? He abandoned the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.43,0:08:13.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.41,0:08:15.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm God's gift to detectives, Mori Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:17.95,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:19.47,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.20,0:08:23.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we got away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.24,0:08:26.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say it like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.21,0:08:27.99,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,You two make a good duo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:33.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like a two hour wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.34,0:08:36.12,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.12,0:08:37.78,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I know the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.13,0:08:40.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We can eat somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:44.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're that guy from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.54,0:08:49.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.36,0:09:01.14,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bleh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:02.64,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.61,0:09:09.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's all he wanted to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.16,0:09:11.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All that trouble just \Nfor that? What an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.93,0:09:12.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.58,0:09:14.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was some drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:18.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were mistaken for a \Nrobber, and even the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.28,0:09:21.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's because we were talking \Nabout that apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.22,0:09:21.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:24.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The place is cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.37,0:09:26.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The apartment is cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.26,0:09:30.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, you rent an apartment \Nthrough a real estate agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:35.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But Kirisaki Remi asked\Nthe landlady directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.68,0:09:37.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,"Do you have any open rooms?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.13,0:09:40.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was drawn to that apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.38,0:09:44.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,"If you're going to kill \Nyourself, do it here."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.87,0:09:46.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.75,0:09:49.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kei-san fell victim to it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.21,0:09:52.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She came back here six months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.09,0:09:56.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but she had planned to \Nreturn after three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.11,0:09:59.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But just before she was supposed to move...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.50,0:10:03.79,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle is postponing the opening \Nof his resort inn by three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:06.54,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't have a job \Nif you went home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.54,0:10:09.89,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine if you want to stay \Nhere for three more months.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.89,0:10:13.67,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, someone new is moving in \Nnext door to you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.94,0:10:17.26,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I hope they're a nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:20.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just after her plans changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.71,0:10:25.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kirisaki Remi moved in and killed \Nherself three months later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.16,0:10:27.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if things had gone \Naccording to her original plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:32.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,she could've avoided the pain \Nof her neighbor's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.27,0:10:40.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The apartment stopped Kei-san to inflict \Nthat painful experience on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.94,0:10:42.57,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:44.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:47.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:48.60,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,We're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.60,0:10:52.68,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I explained someone important \Nto me is visiting from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.68,0:10:54.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Important?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.62,0:11:02.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:04.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.09,0:11:06.43,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Mori-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.74,0:11:09.43,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,this is where I wanted to take you next.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.43,0:11:11.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,An amusement park? That sounds fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.84,0:11:13.94,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,And I recommend this attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:19.74,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.80,0:11:24.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why do they have to have this \Nthing way out in the boonies?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.67,0:11:27.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This really is turning\Ninto the best drive ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.54,0:11:30.12,Dream,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Dream Realized After 10 Years of Planning
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.04,0:11:31.04,Ten,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,"Ten years ago we planned to \Nopen on our silver anniversary."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.53,0:11:30.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the resort inn Kei-san works at.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.81,0:11:34.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But didn't she just say...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.37,0:11:35.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.52,0:11:42.84,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,It was so sunny until a minute ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.20,0:11:45.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a passing shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:47.60,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.03,0:11:54.60,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,It really did pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.92,0:11:57.62,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,The view is wonderful after rain, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.62,0:12:00.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I wish it had kept raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.54,0:12:03.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What was Kirisaki Remi-san like?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.71,0:12:05.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.09,0:12:07.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, she was a brassy woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.98,0:12:10.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant. \NI mean her appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.64,0:12:13.37,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,She had long permed hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.59,0:12:14.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How about glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:16.48,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,No, she didn't wear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.48,0:12:17.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was she fat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.64,0:12:19.75,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,She was on the thin side.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.75,0:12:20.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thinner than you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:22.50,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,About the same, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:25.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was she taller than you? Shorter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:27.39,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I think we were about the same height, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.80,0:12:28.90,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.90,0:12:30.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.16,0:12:32.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you asking now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.44,0:12:38.94,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,That's it, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.21,0:12:40.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.04,0:12:41.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes, it's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.38,0:12:43.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:46.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That suicide was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:13:00.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That brat stole her from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.60,0:13:06.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kei-san, do you have a boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.98,0:13:09.38,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.38,0:13:12.60,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,But he died three years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.99,0:13:14.07,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,of an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:17.98,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Being in Tokyo reminded me of him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.53,0:13:21.11,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,so I decided to come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.45,0:13:29.49,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally alone together...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.94,0:13:32.87,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure we should've \Nleft Conan-kun alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.39,0:13:34.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:35.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a two-person boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.87,0:13:37.37,ToDo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Amusement park? — build excitement!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.61,0:13:40.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Build excitement! Build excitement!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.47,0:13:43.63,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:47.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm totally fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.94,0:13:48.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Probably, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.46,0:13:54.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was her motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:13:59.77,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,The next stop is my number \None recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.21,0:14:02.02,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,The bluffs at Shikabanezaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.50,0:14:03.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's nearly time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:05.40,ToDo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Sunset at the beach — passionate conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.68,0:14:08.66,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to finish the day on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.01,0:14:12.24,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There had to be something \Nbig to make her go that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:16.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They must've caught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.52,0:14:17.87,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.84,0:14:23.30,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry again for the trouble we caused, \Nbut we managed to catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.75,0:14:26.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the culprit had a mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.91,0:14:29.66,DCMain,ROBBER,0000,0000,0000,,I disguised myself with a fake mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.53,0:14:31.55,DCMain,YAMAZUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't brag about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.55,0:14:32.05,DCMain,ROBBER,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.95,0:14:36.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well-built.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.69,0:14:38.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you disguise yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:41.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,there's no disguising your build.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.03,0:14:42.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:44.07,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.17,0:14:48.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's head to the \Nfinish line at Shikabanezaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:49.57,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.46,0:15:01.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This beauty is enough to cleanse your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.09,0:15:02.08,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.47,0:15:05.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no room for evil thoughts here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:10.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.10,0:15:11.59,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.84,0:15:14.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. There's no time to think anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.78,0:15:17.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's the driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.83,0:15:20.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.33,0:15:21.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.03,0:15:24.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't leave now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.66,0:15:27.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All these mysteries are ruining my mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.51,0:15:27.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:29.48,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,What mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.48,0:15:34.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kirisaki Remi-san moved in next door \Njust after you delayed your plans
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.29,0:15:37.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to come back here by three months, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.72,0:15:41.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And she didn't find the place \Nthrough a real estate agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.09,0:15:43.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She asked the landlady directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.69,0:15:46.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And she'd been using fake \Nnames for two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.07,0:15:47.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so why did she rent the \Napartment under her real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.22,0:15:51.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since she left a writing sample on the lease,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:54.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they knew she had written \Nthe suicide note, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.01,0:15:56.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.81,0:15:57.68,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.96,0:16:00.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since her relatives confirmed \Nthe identity of the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.90,0:16:04.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we know it was Kirisaki Remi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.68,0:16:07.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but the descriptions of her don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:13.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since Kei-san came out of \NKirisaki-san's room during the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.54,0:16:17.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we know Kei-san was coming and \Ngoing from Kirisaki-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.36,0:16:20.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But with the exception of \Ntheir hairstyles and glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.22,0:16:22.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they had really similar builds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:24.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.60,0:16:26.71,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see what's so strange about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.14,0:16:28.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The strangest thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:33.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,why you delayed your plans to \Ncome back here by three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.73,0:16:38.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Her uncle delayed his plans \Nto open the resort inn, so—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.54,0:16:39.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.43,0:16:39.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:42.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's an article about Kei-san's uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.79,0:16:45.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It says they planned ten years ago to open
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.49,0:16:49.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,on the day of their silver \Nanniversary, and they did just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.75,0:16:54.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So the opening wasn't delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:59.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Kei-san \Ndelayed her return here
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.17,0:17:02.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,by three months for her own reasons, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:09.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And during those three months...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.83,0:17:10.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.52,0:17:15.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But when you think of it that \Nway, then everything is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.29,0:17:17.66,DCMain,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.07,0:17:20.66,DCMain,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, until the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.66,0:17:25.89,DCMain,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea Nakanishi-san \Nand Kirisaki-san were friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.07,0:17:31.27,DCMain,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I had never \Nseen them together before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.49,0:17:33.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.00,0:17:37.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The woman who hanged herself in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.22,0:17:39.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,next to yours was definitely \NKirisaki Remi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.02,0:17:42.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But she never...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:43.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.67,0:17:47.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody ever lived in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:51.44,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,You saw through my lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.37,0:17:55.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.96,0:17:59.30,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,A grudge from three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.40,0:18:02.81,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I had a fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.81,0:18:05.78,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,His name was Ogawa Natsuyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.78,0:18:09.13,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,When I visited his apartment that \Nday, he was collapsed on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.13,0:18:11.38,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I quickly called an ambulance, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.42,0:18:15.60,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Because of an illegally parked car,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:20.38,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,the ambulance couldn't \Nmake it to his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:24.91,Natsuyuki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Ogawa Natsuyuki (29) \NKei's Boyfriend
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.76,0:18:23.86,DCItalic,OGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kei...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:24.64,DCItalic,OGAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:28.41,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here. I'm right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.26,0:18:34.21,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,He died before we reached the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.68,0:18:39.67,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it was too late by the \Ntime the ambulance arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.55,0:18:44.93,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,But I still thought he may have been \Nsaved if that car hadn't been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:46.87,DCItalic,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,But it seriously sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.87,0:18:49.19,DCItalic,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they never answered their phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.43,0:18:52.69,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I had to say something to the car's owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.06,0:18:54.69,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,But she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.21,0:19:00.68,DCItalic,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,He was just never meant to \Nlive long in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.68,0:19:01.82,DCItalic,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.81,0:19:09.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And that was Kirisaki Remi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.95,0:19:14.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She mocked you and your fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.11,0:19:19.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Three years later, you saw \NKirisaki-san somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.02,0:19:22.26,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,It was three days before I \Nwas going to move back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:34.77,Anzai,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.72,0:19:34.77,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,She used fake names because she \Nwas engaged in some shady business.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.45,0:19:39.28,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,She was a nasty woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.51,0:19:43.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You knew then that you couldn't \Nleave Tokyo like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.44,0:19:46.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,First you had to get revenge \Nfor three years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:47.54,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.85,0:19:51.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when you thought the best way
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:55.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to get away with murder was \Nto make it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:19:59.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So you delayed your return here
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:02.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and became Kirisaki Remi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.41,0:20:04.30,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.52,0:20:06.80,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that room empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:09.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You rented the room next to yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.37,0:20:14.19,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, someone new is moving in \Nnext door to you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.42,0:20:17.81,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I hope they're a nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.37,0:20:23.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Within one apartment, you played both \NNakanishi Kei and Kirisaki Remi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.23,0:20:26.07,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,I want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:29.57,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that, Kirisaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.57,0:20:33.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You began dropping hints so they \Nwould think it's a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.65,0:20:36.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the fire happened, you probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:38.33,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fire, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:39.67,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:43.68,Kirisaki,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Kirisaki
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.03,0:20:41.17,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.17,0:20:42.78,DCItalic,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.90,0:20:44.76,DCItalic,KIYOMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.68,0:20:50.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...had removed your disguise and were \Nabout to return to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.10,0:20:54.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After three months of planning,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.96,0:20:57.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you approached Kirisaki Remi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.37,0:21:02.42,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,You're using a fake name, but \Nyou're Kirisaki Remi-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:04.32,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:07.32,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.96,0:21:12.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You created an excuse to secretly bring \Nher to the neighboring apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.91,0:21:19.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You made it look like a suicide \Nand left a suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.43,0:21:24.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You probably called the \Nlandlord of the apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.16,0:21:26.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,she lived in and asked them \Nto dispose of her belongings,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.58,0:21:28.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,since she'd suddenly decided to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.73,0:21:30.24,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.06,0:21:35.02,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,Will you take me to the police, Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.41,0:21:37.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.31,0:21:45.53,DCMain,KEI,0000,0000,0000,,The sun has set completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.90,0:21:50.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It may have set today, \Nbut it will rise tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.29,0:23:23.29,Police,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Haido Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.52,0:23:26.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Hey, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.09,0:23:28.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.59,0:23:29.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.52,0:23:31.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I just brought in a suspect!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:32.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.67,0:23:36.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I-I'm helping the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.22,0:23:36.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.14,0:23:43.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it would end like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.45,0:23:48.28,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.56,0:23:51.46,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.46,0:23:53.91,DCMain,MITSU,0000,0000,0000,,Something good's happening after this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.91,0:23:59.83,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost Christmas, so I thought we could \Nuse this 10 thousand yen gift certificate...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.14,0:24:05.33,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What was that scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.33,0:24:06.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It came from the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Detectives in a Grove \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.66,0:24:14.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NDetectives in a Grove, Part One!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Christmas Present
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.52,0:24:32.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.94,0:24:34.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A Christmas present!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
